        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">White House in Israel</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-nov-1-2.jpg" alt="White House in Israel" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Senior U.S. officials are in the Middle East to <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c14ln6kkkg7o" target="_blank">negotiate a ceasefire</a> between Israel and Hezbollah. Discussions are ongoing, with the Lebanese Prime Minister expressing cautious optimism. A draft agreement suggests a 60-day ceasefire, during which Israel would withdraw forces from Lebanon, and Hezbollah would cease its armed presence. However, Israel seeks assurances about Hezbollah’s compliance, complicating negotiations.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">There hasn’t been a stop in the violence. Thursday saw attacks from Israel and Hezbollah, resulting in casualties on <a href="https://www.aljazeera.com/news/liveblog/2024/10/31/live-israel-pounds-gaza-lebanon-amid-hopes-of-a-truce-with-hezbollah" target="_blank">both sides</a>. U.S. officials are also aiming for a deal involving hostages in Gaza. Success towards reaching a ceasefire hostage deal has been unsuccessful in the last attempts. Secretary of State Anthony Bliken has visited the Middle East <a href="https://apnews.com/article/us-israel-gaza-lebanon-hamas-blinken-c450119702081057ff6c816d6a19e51a" target="_blank">eleven times</a> in just over a year. See the latest Middle East updates <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/world/live-news/israel-iran-palestine-gaza-war-10-31-24-intl-hnk/index.html" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
