          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇱🇹 Lithuania:</strong> Vilija Blinkeviciute, the leader of Lithuania’s victorious Social Democrats, announced that she would <a href="https://www.politico.eu/article/lithuania-election-winner-refuses-prime-minister-vilija-blinkeviciute/" target="_blank">not assume the role</a> of prime minister, citing concerns about her age and health. At nearly 65 years old and a pensioner, she expressed doubts about her ability to fulfill the demanding responsibilities of the position. Instead, she endorsed <a href="https://pace.coe.int/en/members/8360/paluckas" target="_blank">Gintautas Paluckas</a>, a former party leader, as the best candidate for prime minister. Blinkeviciute prefers to continue serving as a <a href="https://www.europarl.europa.eu/meps/en/96681/VILIJA_BLINKEVICIUTE/home" target="_blank">Member of the European Parliament</a> (MEP) instead of taking a seat in Lithuania’s parliament.</p>
        </mj-text>
